@GrantCuster hrm, the "file locking" section here describes it: https://t.co/p9zg2qxIkj

...you checked out a file, it was locked so that no one else could edit it while you had it, and would remain that way until you checked it in. 

...also, it was terrible?

@nichochar I suspect you're missing the point of my tweet.

It's work. It takes enormous effort and has uncertain timelines and outcomes.

But it's not hard. We know how to do it well.
